>-- so that the FBI's right to tap wires is left undisturbed, keeping the
                      ^^^^^
The FBI does not have a right to tap wires.  If they get a court order,
the communications provider is obligated to proivde assistance, but there
is no provision in current law which makes it a crime for the common
carrier to reply "that data is encryupted so securely there is nothing
we can do" (provided, of course, that such a reply is the truth).

                                        rob b.
